                        {
                            "variable": "tau_OH",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 317460317.46031743
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "k_oh_doubled_matches_oh_doubled_symmetry",
                    "description": "k_OH doubled to 1.26e-20 m^3/s, OH_conc at the default 1.0e12 m^-3. k_eff = k_OH*OH_conc depends only on the product, so k_eff = 1.26e-8 s^-1 and tau_OH = 79365079.36507936 s \u2014 bit-identical to the `oh_conc_doubled_halves_lifetime` result. Verifies the k_OH<->OH_conc product symmetry: doubling the intrinsic reactivity of the species is numerically indistinguishable from doubling the ambient OH. A regression that wired k_eff to only one of the two factors would break exactly one of this test / `oh_conc_doubled_halves_lifetime`.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
