                },
                {
                    "id": "lifetime_heatmap_k_oh_oh_conc",
                    "description": "OH-reaction lifetime as a joint function of species reactivity k_OH and ambient OH concentration (2-D log-log sweep). k_OH in [1.0e-21, 1.0e-16] m^3/s x OH_conc in [1.0e10, 1.0e13] m^-3. Because tau_OH = 1/(k_OH*[OH]) depends only on the product k_OH*[OH], the iso-lifetime contours are straight anti-diagonal lines of constant k_OH*OH_conc: the long-lived corner is the unreactive species in clean air (low k_OH, low OH), the short-lived corner is the reactive species in polluted air (high k_OH, high OH). Surfaces the full bivariate structure that the two 1-D sweeps each section.",
                    "time_span": {
